  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Urban Greece: Supporting Refugees (UGSR) Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UPDATE : As HRC is currently under suspension. Future plans to support the MFC are on hold. BRC had already committed to supporting the MFC until June 2019 and have agreed to a no-cost-extension until August 2019. A case study is to be completed on Peer to Peer Model that formed part of this project. The HRC will increase its capacity to meet the needs of migrants living in urban centres by relocating and enhancing its existing multifunctional centre in Athens and establishing an additional multifunctional centre in Thessaloniki. This project focuses on the latter as the MFC in Athens will be supported by the Danish Red Cross (DRC). The MFC in Thessaloniki will provide migrants with a centrally located and accessible entry point to a range of Red Cross services designed to support the needs of the most vulnerable. Services available to migrants will include access to casework services that can provide up to date information and guidance assisted orientation delivered by trained volunteers language support psycho-social support services cash assistance and access to Restoring Family Links services. The centre where appropriate will also host a range of outreach services designed to meet the needs of migrants located in areas where there is a clearly identified lack of direct service provision.</narrative>
  </description>
